Package projects.pqueue.lists

Interface List<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of object that the List will hold.
    All Superinterfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DoublyLinkedList, LinkedList, StaticArrayList
    public interface List<T>
extends java.lang.Iterable<T>

    A List is a linear ADT which offers insertion, search and deletion in at most linear time. Elements can only be added to the front or the back, never in between.

    It is a requirement that the type T is Comparable, or else we will not be able to implement methods such as contains(Object) and delete(int). The interface is Iterable interface, which means that we can use for-each loops to easily access its elements.

    You should not edit this class! It is given to you as a resource for your project.
